The paper presents a fast algorithm for approximate Canonical Correlation Analysis (CCA) that employs randomized dimensionality reduction transform to reduce the size of the input matrices. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). However, given that the paper focuses on a machine learning algorithm, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also possible because the paper involves information theory, data structures and algorithms, social and information networks, and artificial intelligence.
